column3: Altitude Day 8 - Pikes Peak or Bust
column5:
Pikes peak hill climb race, finished 9th in catagory, with a time of 1:32:51. Goal was sub-90' but fell a bit short at the end when the altitude got to me. Was hyperventilating a bit so couldnt get my heart rate up to my threshold as i wanted. Pacing was good though, had enough to push through at the end despite the heavy legs. 
This marks the end of my base phase and time to move into build-up for cyclocross. I think I have a good base to build some strength on the cross course.
